[phone disconnects]

788
00:46:06,660 --> 00:46:07,787
[exhales]

789
00:46:11,290 --> 00:46:14,293
[car engine revving]

790
00:46:16,087 --> 00:46:17,254
[exhales]

791
00:46:17,630 --> 00:46:19,465
My aunt.
Someone's in her hospital room.

792
00:46:19,799 --> 00:46:20,800
Huh?

793
00:46:21,717 --> 00:46:23,010
[gasps]
[phone chimes]

794
00:46:23,094 --> 00:46:25,888
[phone trilling]

795
00:46:25,971 --> 00:46:27,640
[Nurse B] Saebaek Hospital, oncology ward.

796
00:46:28,057 --> 00:46:29,892
Hi, this is Ms. Yeo Sunok's guardian.

797
00:46:29,975 --> 00:46:32,103
Can--can you send someone
to check on her, please?

798
00:46:32,186 --> 00:46:36,065
It seems someone's--there's--there's
someone strange in her room right now.

799
00:46:36,148 --> 00:46:39,485
[distant sirens blaring]

800
00:46:45,574 --> 00:46:47,118
[tires squeal]

801
00:46:49,870 --> 00:46:53,749
[tires squeak]

802
00:47:02,716 --> 00:47:05,719
[engine rumbling]
STYLE
::cue()

803
00:47:28,033 --> 00:47:31,036
[♪ suspenseful music]

804
00:47:47,094 --> 00:47:49,346
[rumbling]

805
00:47:54,643 --> 00:47:55,644
[brakes squeak]

806
00:48:12,745 --> 00:48:14,747
[brakes squeal]

807
00:48:21,378 --> 00:48:22,379
[headlights click]

808
00:48:23,130 --> 00:48:24,131
[sniffs]

809
00:48:41,398 --> 00:48:42,816
[brakes squeak]

810
00:48:44,485 --> 00:48:45,486
[car engine shuts off]

811
00:48:48,989 --> 00:48:50,449
[phone chimes and trills]

812
00:48:50,533 --> 00:48:53,536
[cell phone vibrating]

813
00:48:56,455 --> 00:48:57,456
Hello?

814
00:48:58,207 --> 00:48:59,625
Where are you, Detective Kim?

815
00:49:02,711 --> 00:49:04,463
[Jinman] Uh, I'm at the office right now.

816
00:49:04,838 --> 00:49:06,882
It's a busy night
so I'm doing some overtime.

817
00:49:08,968 --> 00:49:09,969
[Hocheol] Really?

818
00:49:10,719 --> 00:49:14,431
So that gray SUV I see,
that's not your car?

819
00:49:15,057 --> 00:49:17,184
Why'd you ask me
if you knew where I was?

820
00:49:22,314 --> 00:49:23,774
How long have you been following me?

821
00:49:24,316 --> 00:49:25,609
Since the hospital.

822
00:49:26,151 --> 00:49:27,152
Mm.

823
00:49:27,236 --> 00:49:28,988
[lighter clicking]

824
00:49:30,030 --> 00:49:32,449
Tell me. How much do you know, then?

825
00:49:33,075 --> 00:49:34,076
[Hocheol] Ju Haran?

826
00:49:34,952 --> 00:49:37,371
Ju Haran is a person you took care
of long ago.

827
00:49:38,747 --> 00:49:41,166
As soon as I gave you all her information
she went missing.

828
00:49:42,876 --> 00:49:43,961
Hmm.

829
00:49:45,004 --> 00:49:46,088
I remember.

830
00:49:47,798 --> 00:49:48,799
What about...

831
00:49:49,466 --> 00:49:50,467
...Kim Heeju?

832
00:49:56,599 --> 00:49:58,767
[Hocheol] You really know how
to sniff things out.

833
00:49:59,977 --> 00:50:03,147
You're like a fucking dog, Detective Kim.

834
00:50:04,315 --> 00:50:05,316
[lips smack]

835
00:50:05,983 --> 00:50:07,109
What are you talking about?

836
00:50:07,651 --> 00:50:08,652
Huh?

837
00:50:08,986 --> 00:50:10,195
Kim Heeju? Who's that?

838
00:50:12,072 --> 00:50:14,950
Ah. Yeah. Yangpo Airport.

839
00:50:15,034 --> 00:50:16,368
She's on the security team.

840
00:50:16,702 --> 00:50:18,746
Have you told Chairman
Ahn about Kim Heeju?

841
00:50:19,455 --> 00:50:22,374
You're here all by yourself,
so I bet you haven't, right?

842
00:50:24,126 --> 00:50:25,127
[Hocheol] Well, then.

843
00:50:26,754 --> 00:50:28,005
That means we have the same goal.

844
00:50:28,797 --> 00:50:30,090
What the hell are you saying?

845
00:50:30,799 --> 00:50:33,552
I just do what I'm told, Park.
You should already know that.

846
00:50:34,595 --> 00:50:36,889
The Chairman told me to find you
so that's what I'm doing.

847
00:50:37,556 --> 00:50:40,893
Whoever gets to Kim Heeju first gets all
the gold. Right?

848
00:50:41,935 --> 00:50:45,272
And the two of us are the only ones
who know that Kim Heeju has the gold.

849
00:50:45,981 --> 00:50:47,066
[exhales]

850
00:50:47,900 --> 00:50:49,318
Park, listen.

851
00:50:49,777 --> 00:50:52,613
I couldn't care less about who takes
the gold bars.

852
00:50:52,696 --> 00:50:54,365
I really don't give a shit.

853
00:50:54,448 --> 00:50:55,949
So one of us has to fucking die!

854
00:50:56,033 --> 00:50:58,702
[car engine revving]

855
00:50:58,786 --> 00:51:00,746
[crashing]

856
00:51:00,829 --> 00:51:03,749
[tires squealing]

857
00:51:08,712 --> 00:51:10,339
[breathing heavily]

858
00:51:10,422 --> 00:51:13,384
[Hocheol breathing erratically]

859
00:51:24,061 --> 00:51:26,980
[glass clinking]

860
00:51:27,064 --> 00:51:30,067
[engine rumbling]
STYLE
::cue()

861
00:51:48,836 --> 00:51:51,839
[distant sirens blaring]

862
00:51:53,090 --> 00:51:55,884
GANGWON SAEBAEK HOSPITAL

863
00:51:55,968 --> 00:51:58,971
[machines beeping]

864
00:52:06,520 --> 00:52:07,813
Geez, what happened to you?

865
00:52:07,896 --> 00:52:11,483
Huh? Oh, you're here.
Help me up. Shit.

866
00:52:11,859 --> 00:52:13,402
[groaning]

867
00:52:13,485 --> 00:52:14,903
Fuck me.

868
00:52:14,987 --> 00:52:17,156
[groaning]

869
00:52:17,781 --> 00:52:19,742
Look at me.
I almost died.

870
00:52:21,160 --> 00:52:22,411
What happened?

871
00:52:23,245 --> 00:52:25,080
Park, that fucking piece of shit,

872
00:52:25,164 --> 00:52:28,500
threatened to kill me and then he just
straight up rammed me with his car.

873
00:52:28,584 --> 00:52:29,752
-[Jinman] Dammit.
-What?

874
00:52:30,669 --> 00:52:32,337
[Jinman] Hey, by the way.

875
00:52:32,921 --> 00:52:34,506
What did you find out?

876
00:52:35,007 --> 00:52:37,468
You're the one who told Park about
the hospital.

877
00:52:37,551 --> 00:52:42,014
Yeah. He said it would settle
my Geumseong debts.

878
00:52:42,097 --> 00:52:43,223
[exhales sharply]

879
00:52:43,932 --> 00:52:44,933
[smacks lips]

880
00:52:50,147 --> 00:52:51,482
[Jinman] Listen.

881
00:52:51,565 --> 00:52:52,941
Once Park finds her...

882
00:52:54,067 --> 00:52:55,819
...Ju Haran is a dead woman.

883
00:52:56,779 --> 00:52:58,906
It doesn't matter if she has
the casket or not.

884
00:52:59,698 --> 00:53:01,825
He's gonna kill her either way.

885
00:53:02,743 --> 00:53:05,370
[Jinman] If you knew about that
and still helped Park find her...

886
00:53:07,206 --> 00:53:08,707
...then you shouldn't be a police officer.

887
00:53:10,000 --> 00:53:11,668
You're just an asshole.

888
00:53:12,169 --> 00:53:13,962
[Jinman] Park has no ties
to Geumseong anymore.

889
00:53:14,046 --> 00:53:15,380
He can't settle your debt.

890
00:53:16,006 --> 00:53:19,343
He's just doing whatever it takes
to find the casket and then get out.

891
00:53:24,097 --> 00:53:26,767
You know he killed Cheon, right?

892
00:53:28,268 --> 00:53:29,353
[Jinman] Chairman Ahn wants Park dead.

893
00:53:29,436 --> 00:53:32,231
And that's why his men are crawling
all over Jeongsan right now.

894
00:53:32,940 --> 00:53:33,941
Did you know that?

895
00:53:35,734 --> 00:53:37,110
I kinda knew, yeah.

896
00:53:37,194 --> 00:53:39,029
And you still said yes?

897
00:53:39,112 --> 00:53:40,239
[Jinman] Huh?

898
00:53:40,322 --> 00:53:42,491
Chairman Ahn is gonna catch Park soon,

899
00:53:42,574 --> 00:53:44,868
and when he does we both know
what's gonna happen.

900
00:53:46,578 --> 00:53:49,206
You think a dead man
can help settle your debt?

901
00:53:50,415 --> 00:53:51,416
[Jinman] How much was it?

902
00:53:52,209 --> 00:53:53,335
Around 100 million won?

903
00:53:54,169 --> 00:53:55,462
If I bring back the gold...

904
00:53:56,088 --> 00:53:57,631
...the Chairman's promised to pay me.

905
00:53:57,714 --> 00:53:59,383
[Jinman] I can settle your debt.

906
00:53:59,883 --> 00:54:01,051
Do you mean that?

907
00:54:01,134 --> 00:54:02,135
Want it in writing?

908
00:54:04,054 --> 00:54:05,430
[exhales]

909
00:54:05,514 --> 00:54:07,724
Wh--What am I supposed to tell Park?

910
00:54:07,808 --> 00:54:11,562
Just tell Park you're still looking
or something, 'kay?

911
00:54:12,145 --> 00:54:14,481
You just need to keep it vague, yeah?

912
00:54:15,357 --> 00:54:17,985
Hold him off until I get the casket back
to Chairman Ahn.

913
00:54:18,777 --> 00:54:21,947
Say whatever you need
to string him along, yeah?

914
00:54:22,239 --> 00:54:23,699
[Jinman] That son of a bitch Park...

915
00:54:24,533 --> 00:54:26,994
...he's definitely gonna die soon, got it?

916
00:54:27,661 --> 00:54:29,204
So you think this through.

917
00:54:29,288 --> 00:54:31,540
[inhales and exhales sharply]

918
00:54:31,623 --> 00:54:32,624
Okay.

919
00:54:32,708 --> 00:54:34,918
[breathing erratically]

920
00:54:41,341 --> 00:54:44,344
[light pained breathing]

921
00:54:54,605 --> 00:54:57,608
You're Yes Money guys, huh?

922
00:54:58,609 --> 00:54:59,610
Why are you here?

923
00:54:59,985 --> 00:55:01,153
[exhales]

924
00:55:01,236 --> 00:55:02,904
Well, it's a hospital, you know?

925
00:55:02,988 --> 00:55:04,698
We're all here to see the doctor.

926
00:55:05,616 --> 00:55:07,242
This is the oncology ward.

927
00:55:08,243 --> 00:55:09,453
You have cancer?

928
00:55:09,536 --> 00:55:10,996
Yeah.

929
00:55:12,039 --> 00:55:14,207
Oh, really? All of them, too?

930
00:55:16,126 --> 00:55:18,629
-Yeah.
-[groans]

931
00:55:19,421 --> 00:55:21,882
Give this message to Ko, 'kay?

932
00:55:23,008 --> 00:55:25,719
You have until the end of the day
to get all of your men outta here.

933
00:55:26,887 --> 00:55:30,724
Or I'll have to take everyone in
for obstruction of business. Got it?

934
00:55:30,807 --> 00:55:32,309
[breathing machine hissing]

935
00:55:32,392 --> 00:55:33,393
[grunts]

936
00:55:35,020 --> 00:55:36,021
Here?

937
00:55:42,944 --> 00:55:45,238
[groaning]

938
00:55:47,741 --> 00:55:49,201
[exhales]

939
00:55:54,373 --> 00:55:55,415
What?

940
00:56:07,928 --> 00:56:09,763
[water splashes]

941
00:56:10,514 --> 00:56:11,932
[Mija] Yeah, I got rid of it.

942
00:56:12,808 --> 00:56:14,017
What about the detective?

943
00:56:14,101 --> 00:56:15,936
[Mija] I told you.
He's not here.

944
00:56:16,019 --> 00:56:18,021
[inhales and exhales sharply]
STYLE
::cue()

945
00:56:18,522 --> 00:56:19,940
I'll be there soon, okay?

946
00:56:20,982 --> 00:56:22,275
[Heeju] Can you stay with her?

947
00:56:22,359 --> 00:56:24,069
At least until I get there?

948
00:56:24,152 --> 00:56:25,570
Okay.

949
00:56:26,488 --> 00:56:27,572
[exhales sharply]

950
00:56:27,656 --> 00:56:29,908
Are you really gonna move her
somewhere else?

951
00:56:29,991 --> 00:56:32,953
[Mija] Do we have to?
She's still unconscious.

952
00:56:33,036 --> 00:56:36,540
We got rid of the bug
so why not just keep her here?

953
00:56:36,623 --> 00:56:38,458
Won't the detective find her anyway?

954
00:56:38,542 --> 00:56:39,918
We can talk when I'm there.

955
00:56:40,001 --> 00:56:41,503
[Mija] Fine.

956
00:56:42,629 --> 00:56:43,630
[phone disconnects]

957
00:56:44,506 --> 00:56:47,509
[Woogy grunting]

958
00:56:48,135 --> 00:56:49,136
Hey.

959
00:56:49,678 --> 00:56:51,388
Just go to a doctor.

960
00:56:51,471 --> 00:56:52,597
Why would I do that?

961
00:56:55,559 --> 00:56:57,185
-Just go.
-[Heeju exhales sharply]

962
00:56:59,104 --> 00:57:01,022
[groans]

963
00:57:11,032 --> 00:57:13,326
Excuse me?

964
00:57:13,410 --> 00:57:15,328
Will you call Kim Heeju
and let her know I'm here?

965
00:57:16,621 --> 00:57:18,957
I need to talk to her.
Ask her to call me.

966
00:57:19,875 --> 00:57:22,419
K--Kim Heeju?

967
00:57:22,502 --> 00:57:25,630
I don't know anyone by that name.

968
00:57:26,339 --> 00:57:28,592
I don't have her number, either.
[chuckles]

969
00:57:29,342 --> 00:57:30,552
Mija.

970
00:57:31,595 --> 00:57:32,888
[Jinman] You really don't recognize me?

971
00:57:33,805 --> 00:57:35,640
I was stationed at Jeongsan.

972
00:57:35,724 --> 00:57:37,851
Kim Jinman.
I was a constable then.

973
00:57:40,228 --> 00:57:42,230
[Jinman] Well, it's been 30 years,
I guess.

974
00:57:43,523 --> 00:57:44,649
Don't you remember?

975
00:57:45,525 --> 00:57:47,944
Sunok and I lived together
for around a year.

976
00:57:48,028 --> 00:57:49,029
[Mija] Uh...

977
00:57:50,113 --> 00:57:51,281
[Jinman] You remember me, right?

978
00:57:51,364 --> 00:57:53,950
[chuckles nervously]

979
00:58:01,249 --> 00:58:02,250
[groans]

980
00:58:02,334 --> 00:58:03,376
[phone chimes]

981
00:58:03,877 --> 00:58:06,880
[phone trilling]

982
00:58:07,964 --> 00:58:10,967
[cell phone vibrating]

983
00:58:12,594 --> 00:58:14,554
-Yeah, Aunt Mija?
-[Mija] Heeju.

984
00:58:14,638 --> 00:58:17,390
- Detective Kim is here right now.
-What?

985
00:58:27,859 --> 00:58:29,152
Here you go.

986
00:58:29,236 --> 00:58:30,987
Heeju. There.

987
00:58:35,075 --> 00:58:36,076
[exhales]

988
00:58:39,204 --> 00:58:42,290
[door slides open and closed]

989
00:58:44,167 --> 00:58:45,168
Kim Heeju?

990
00:58:46,586 --> 00:58:48,338
It's Detective Kim Jinman.

991
00:58:49,214 --> 00:58:50,465
[Jinman] All right, then.

992
00:58:51,132 --> 00:58:53,468
You need to listen to me very carefully,
okay?

993
00:58:54,219 --> 00:58:57,180
Obviously, I know you have the casket.
And so does Park.

994
00:58:59,850 --> 00:59:02,727
You need to stay away from the hospital.

995
00:59:03,520 --> 00:59:06,398
[Jinman] I've got everything covered here
so don't worry about that.

996
00:59:08,400 --> 00:59:09,526
Listen, Kim Heeju.

997
00:59:12,153 --> 00:59:13,154
Park and I...

998
00:59:14,030 --> 00:59:17,659
...we're--we're really different, okay?

999
00:59:18,827 --> 00:59:21,621
Park is the kind of person who will stop
at nothing to find you.

1000
00:59:22,455 --> 00:59:24,875
He's so much more evil
than anyone could even imagine.

1001
00:59:24,958 --> 00:59:26,459
I really mean it, Heeju.

1002
00:59:27,460 --> 00:59:29,713
[Jinman] You need to stop wasting time.

1003
00:59:31,172 --> 00:59:34,092
Stop dragging this out and just tell
me where the casket is, Heeju.

1004
00:59:35,385 --> 00:59:38,138
We need to return that thing
to Chairman Ahn.

1005
00:59:38,221 --> 00:59:39,472
Today.

1006
00:59:39,556 --> 00:59:41,349
[Woogy exhales]

1007
00:59:41,433 --> 00:59:44,644
If you don't, Chairman Ahn
and Park Hocheol won't leave you alone.

1008
00:59:45,228 --> 00:59:48,023
I'm telling you they won't ever
stop looking for you.

1009
00:59:48,106 --> 00:59:50,317
[Jinman] Okay? Do you understand?

1010
00:59:56,781 --> 00:59:58,366
[phone disconnects]
[Heeju] Hey.

1011
00:59:58,450 --> 00:59:59,910
[phone disconnects]

1012
01:00:04,581 --> 01:00:06,082
[pained exhale]

1013
01:00:08,752 --> 01:00:11,755
[breathing machine hisses]

1014
01:00:15,508 --> 01:00:16,509
Hey.

1015
01:00:18,762 --> 01:00:19,930
Sunok.

1016
01:00:21,848 --> 01:00:22,974
[Jinman] Yeo Sunok.

1017
01:00:27,520 --> 01:00:29,147
I'll save your daughter, okay?

1018
01:00:34,945 --> 01:00:37,030
[Jinman] So don't worry.
Just rest up.

1019
01:00:37,155 --> 01:00:40,408
[groans]
Shit.

1020
01:00:40,492 --> 01:00:41,493
Heeju.

1021
01:00:44,871 --> 01:00:46,206
Should we do what he says?
STYLE
::cue()

1022
01:00:48,667 --> 01:00:50,669
Should we just give
the chairman back his gold?

1023
01:00:51,962 --> 01:00:53,129
[Woogy] He might be right.

1024
01:00:54,089 --> 01:00:55,382
Maybe we should hand it all over.

1025
01:00:55,757 --> 01:00:57,384
Before he finds out it's you.

1026
01:00:58,176 --> 01:00:59,636
[Woogy] I think it'd be better that way.

1027
01:01:02,555 --> 01:01:03,556
Heeju.

1028
01:01:04,474 --> 01:01:06,017
You saw it yesterday.

1029
01:01:07,519 --> 01:01:08,561
If they catch you...

1030
01:01:09,938 --> 01:01:11,856
...the things they do
will be worse than death.

1031
01:01:11,940 --> 01:01:15,151
Even if Detective Kim is really planning
to return the gold to Ahn,

1032
01:01:15,235 --> 01:01:16,486
it's too late now.

1033
01:01:17,278 --> 01:01:18,780
I gave half to Lee Dokyung.

1034
01:01:19,489 --> 01:01:21,157
It's not possible to return it.

1035
01:01:24,369 --> 01:01:26,329
[exhales]

1036
01:01:31,710 --> 01:01:32,711
[clicks tongue]

1037
01:01:42,387 --> 01:01:43,930
And besides.

1038
01:01:46,307 --> 01:01:49,686
Do you really think you can give up
the gold now?

1039
01:01:49,769 --> 01:01:53,314
[Heeju] Just return it and go back
to the way things were before?

1040
01:01:56,317 --> 01:01:59,320
[♪ dramatic music]

1041
01:02:01,239 --> 01:02:02,365
I know I can't.

1042
01:02:04,868 --> 01:02:05,994
[exhales]

1043
01:02:11,249 --> 01:02:14,252
[♪ music continues]

1044
01:02:49,245 --> 01:02:52,248
[♪ dramatic music]

1045
